						<summary>

						<p>Aparādhakshamēśvara Temple-Central Shrine, south wall.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Vikrama-chōḷa (?)</hi></p>						

						<p>This inscription is very much damaged.</p>						

						<p>It records an undertaking by some of the <hi rend="italic">śivabrāhmaṇas</hi> to contribute interest in paddy for the conduct of various services apparently for God Tirukkuraṅgāḍu-tuṟai-uḍaiya-nāyaṉār in the temple at Iṟaiyāṉ-puñjei, on taking over a deposit of paddy as capital.</p>						

						</summary>
